acptoapi is THE SDK for freddie (since 1.0.59 / 2026-05-13). Do NOT reimplement LLM resolution, chain fallback, sampler backoff, or matrix-aware scoring in freddie. acptoapi is the single source of truth. src/agent/llm_resolver.js is a 61-line thin shim over acptoapi.chat({model, messages, tools, queuesMap, matrixSource, onFallback, output}). It builds a comma-list model string from [explicit, input.model, agent.model_preference, keyed buildAutoChain] and delegates everything else. Consume these acptoapi top-level exports directly (no re-export shim): chat, stream, chain, chatChain, streamChain, fallback, buildAutoChain, resolveModel, parseCommaList, splitPrefix, listAllModelsAndQueues, resolveQueue, listAllQueues, loadMatrix, matrixScore, clearMatrixCache, peekStatus, getStatus, isAvailable, markFailed, markOk, resetAvailability, startSampler, stopSampler, createSampler, probe, probeModels, getCachedModels, getRunHistory, PROVIDER_KEYS, PROVIDER_DEFAULTS. Acceptable freddie-side adapters that cannot be deleted: model-discovery.js (claude-cli/ACP/ollama probing breadth acptoapi doesn't cover), model-matrix.js (matrix file path is repo-local), acptoapi-bridge.js (HTTP daemon passthrough at FREDDIE_LLM_URL).